file-name: XC593119-Ruby-cheeked Sunbird-call-1-1-Xeno-Kledang-Sayong Forest Reserve, Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia-17th August 2020.mp3
rmk: These are from call recordings made of a self-feeding, immature male. Different sources have described song and calls in different ways with trills, chirps and a variety of other notes. I have heard much variation in the calls and songs. One call used has some similarity in the sonogram but are used in a variety of different ways - as single notes, 0.2 seconds long. These can be used as coupled notes (2-5 notes) in a run. Finally the same call can be extended (up to 0.4 seconds) to give a longer drawn-out call or slurred note. There is a group of sharper, briefer (0.1 seconds), higher frequency calls that are often used in runs of 3-6 notes.
An adult male and a juvenile male seen. The adult male was incessantly flicking its tail up and down while caling to the juvenile, and the younger bird kept hopping away from it.
